# ZERODRIFT — Figma Implementation

Figma is source. Code is replica. Overlay test is acceptance criterion.
For advanced effects (blend modes, backdrop-filter): load `references/figma-advanced.md`

---

## DEFINITION OF DONE — Photoshop Overlay Test

```
1. Open browser at Figma frame width (1920 or 1440)
2. Full-page screenshot
3. Export Figma frame at 1x
4. Photoshop: overlay, Multiply blend, 50% opacity, zoom 100%

PASS: nothing visible — shapes merge, colors match, text aligns
FAIL: any outline, offset, shift = NOT DONE — fix before marking complete
```

---

## F1 — Typography: 7 properties, all required

```css
font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;  /* exact name — not system-ui */
font-size: 13px;                   /* NOT 14px */
font-weight: 500;                  /* numeric — not "medium" */
line-height: 20px;                 /* px — not 1.5 unless Figma shows 1.5 */
letter-spacing: -0.02em;           /* sign + decimals */
text-transform: uppercase;         /* if Figma has it */
color: #1A1A2E;                    /* exact hex */
```

If font is paid → purchase license. Never substitute.

---

## F2 — Colors: exact hex, grays are different

```css
/* #6B7180 ≠ #6B7280. Both intentional. Copy exact. */
:root {
  --color-text-primary:   #0A0A0A;
  --color-text-secondary: #6B7180;
  --color-text-muted:     #9CA3AF;
  --color-border:         #E5E7EB;
  --color-surface:        #F9FAFB;
}
```

---

## F3 — Visible layers only

```
✅ Extract: visible=true, opacity>0, within frame
❌ Skip:    hidden (eye OFF), opacity=0, outside frame,
            named "ref"/"guide"/"DO NOT USE", inside hidden parent
```

---

## F4 — Auto Layout → CSS

```
direction: horizontal  →  flex-direction: row
direction: vertical    →  flex-direction: column
item spacing: N        →  gap: Npx
padding T/R/B/L        →  padding: Tpx Rpx Bpx Lpx
align: center          →  align-items: center
justify: space-between →  justify-content: space-between
fill container         →  width: 100%
hug contents           →  width: fit-content
fixed: 320             →  width: 320px
min/max                →  min-width / max-width
wrap: wrap             →  flex-wrap: wrap
```

Nested Auto Layout = nested flex. Every level. Every property. Nothing skipped.

---

## F5 — Viewport scaling (1920 → actual)

```
Scale formula: figma_value × (viewport / 1920)
At 1440px: all values × 0.75

Fluid: clamp(min, vw_value, figma_value)
  vw_value = (figma_value / 1920) * 100

Example: Figma gap 48px
  gap: clamp(32px, 2.5vw, 48px);

Breakpoints ONLY from Figma frames — never invent.
```

---

## F6 — Shadows: exact X/Y/blur/spread/color/opacity

```css
/* Figma Effects: X:0 Y:4 Blur:24 Spread:0 #000 12% */
box-shadow: 0px 4px 24px 0px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
/* Multiple shadows: Figma order = CSS order */
```

---

## F7 — Border radius: per corner when mixed

```css
/* Figma: TL=8 TR=8 BR=0 BL=0 */
border-radius: 8px 8px 0 0;
/* NEVER: border-radius: 8px (when corners differ) */
```

